---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import CTABanner from '../components/CTABanner.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About FNE | Figma Naming Enforcer"
  description="FNE is an LLM-powered tool that audits and auto-fixes Figma layer names against natural language naming standards. Open source, MIT licensed."
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="bg-primary-50 px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl font-bold text-primary-900 md:text-5xl">About FNE</h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-primary-600">
          LLM-powered Figma layer naming audit and fix. Built for designers who care about file quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900">The Problem</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-primary-600">
          <p>
            Figma files accumulate hundreds of poorly named layers. Defaults like "Frame 1,"
            appearance-based names like "blue button," and vague labels like "container" create
            cascading problems. AI design-to-code tools cannot interpret them. Manual renaming
            does not scale. Teams cannot enforce standards.
          </p>
          <p>
            FNE uses Claude AI to analyze every layer name against a configurable naming standard,
            then generates a reviewable manifest of suggested renames. A companion Figma plugin
            applies those renames safely with preview, selective application, and rollback.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12 font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900">Key Insight</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-primary-600">
          <p>
            Separate read from write. The CLI never modifies your Figma file. All changes go
            through a human-reviewable JSON manifest before execution. The manifest is the contract
            between the CLI and the plugin.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12 font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900">Principles</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-primary-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900">Manifest as Contract</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-primary-600">All changes are reviewed as JSON before execution. Nothing is hidden.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-primary-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900">Non-Destructive</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-primary-600">The plugin verifies old names match before renaming. Rollback up to 10 operations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-primary-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900">Confidence Tiers</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-primary-600">Users control risk tolerance via high, medium, and low confidence filtering.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-primary-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900">Open Source</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-primary-600">MIT licensed. Free CLI and Figma plugin. Design system maintainers need to trust the tools that modify their files.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12 font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900">Built by Halisonworks</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-primary-600">
          <p>
            FNE is built and maintained by Halisonworks AS, based in Norway.
            We build tools for designers and developers who care about quality at the detail level.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <CTABanner
      headline="Clean Figma names. 10 minutes. 500 layers."
      ctaText="Install FNE"
      ctaHref="#quickstart"
      variant="accent"
    />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
